        {
            "text": "It has been demonstrated that lap-cholecystectomy for acute cholecystitis is a high-risk procedure in elderly patients with comorbidities. Endoscopic ultrasound-guided gallbladder drainage (EUS-GBD), which is already considered an effective alternative to surgery, may now see its indications expanded if intensive care resources and operating rooms are overwhelmed [5] [6] [7] [8] . During the COVID-19 crisis in Italy, our multidisciplinary team has started favoring EUS-GBD over percutaneous drainage in order to obtain a definitive treatment that potentially allows rapid patient discharge. Indeed, our group previously reported that EUS-GBD could be performed without general anesthesia in up to 90% of cases, leading to very low anesthesiological complications and ICU admissions [9, 10] .",
